cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in research, please cite it as below."
title: "Runtime Contracts for Local Agents Over Sensitive User-Owned Data"
abstract: >-
  A runtime-contract research project studying whether enforceable local
  software contracts can make smaller local models viable operators for
  bounded workflows over sensitive user-owned data. HAI is the
  personal-wellness reference runtime; GovernedAgentBench is the benchmark
  scaffold.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Dom
    family-names: Colligan
repository-code: "https://github.com/dtcolligan/health_agent_infra"
url: "https://github.com/dtcolligan/health_agent_infra"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - personal-health
  - LLM-agents
  - runtime-enforcement
  - runtime-contracts
  - agent-evals
  - GovernedAgentBench
  - local-first
  - deterministic-policy
  - intervals.icu
  - garmin
  - claude-code
version: "0.2.0"
date-released: "2026-05-07"
